ud from the mohole, and landed on the opposite shore. Discussions about the aquifer's rupture and the flooding of the basin occurred.","relationships":[{"location":"Bakhuysen","relationship":"Linked by the piste route"},{"location":"Margaritifer station","relationship":"Connected via flight path"}]},{"name":"Bakhuysen","aliases":["Bakhuysen airstrip"],"description":"A rebel stronghold in the southern hemisphere, featuring a crater-wall hangar and a network of underground shelters.","recentEvents":"The travelers were greeted by rebels escaping Korolyov Prime, who shared intel about the war on Mars and Phobos. They received supplies and directions to Margaritifer station.","relationships":[{"location":"Margaritifer station","relationship":"Linked by flight path"},{"location":"Korolyov Prime","relationship":"Previously occupied by rebels"}]},{"name":"Margaritifer station","aliases":[],"description":"A weather station in the northern hemisphere, serving as a refuge for rebels and a hub for communication and supplies.","recentEvents":"The travelers arrived after being directed by Bakhuysen rebels, where they met Arkady's followers and learned about the Clarke cable's sabotage.","relationships":[{"location":"Clarke","relationship":"Linked by the cable's descent trajectory"}]},{"name":"Clarke","aliases":["Clarke asteroid"],"description":"A massive space station orbiting Mars, connected to the planet by a solar power cable.","recentEvents":"The cable was severed by rebels, causing Clarke to drift away from Mars and the solar system. Its descent path was calculated and monitored.","relationships":[{"location":"Phobos","relationship":"Used as a surveillance and attack station"},{"location":"Olympus Mons","relationship":"Previously occupied by rebels"}]}],"arcSnapshots":[{"name":"Cultural Resistance and Martian Autonomy","status":"active","characters":["Nadia Cherneshevsky","Ann Clayborne","Sax Russell","Steve","Arkady Bogdanov"],"summary":"The sabotage of the Clarke cable by 